{"id": "887", "instruction": "What is the equation for the surface of revolution resulting from the rotation of line\n${\\frac{x} {2}}={\\frac{y} {1}}={\\frac{z-1} {0}}$ around line $x=y=z$ ?\n\nOptions:\nA. $$\n3 ( x^{2}+y^{2}+z^{2} )-5 ( x y+x z+y z )+5 ( x+y+z )-7=0\n$$\nB. $$\n( x^{2}+y^{2}+z^{2} )-4 ( x y+x z+y z )+5 ( x+y+z )-7=0\n$$\nC. $$\n2 ( x^{2}+y^{2}+z^{2} )-5 ( x y+x z+y z )+5 ( x+y+z )-7=0\n$$\nD. $$\n( x^{2}+y^{2}+z^{2} )- ( x y+x z+y z )+5 ( x+y+z )-7=0\n$$\nE. $$\n2 ( x^{2}+y^{2}+z^{2} )-5 ( x y+x z+y z )+5 ( x+y+z )-5=0\n$$\nF. $$\n5 ( x^{2}+y^{2}+z^{2} )-5 ( x y+x z+y z )+5 ( x+y+z )-7=0\n$$\nG. $$\n4 ( x^{2}+y^{2}+z^{2} )-5 ( x y+x z+y z )+5 ( x+y+z )-7=0\n$$\nH. $$\n( x^{2}+y^{2}+z^{2} )-5 ( x y+x z+y z )+5 ( x+y+z )-7=0\n$$\nI. $$\n( x^{2}+y^{2}+z^{2} )-2 ( x y+x z+y z )+5 ( x+y+z )-7=0\n$$\nJ. $$\n( x^{2}+y^{2}+z^{2} )-3 ( x y+x z+y z )+5 ( x+y+z )-7=0\n$$", "output": "C"}
